speech.p: Is my right hon. Friend aware of this morning’s appalling news that a Russian bomber has been shot down by a NATO country, Turkey? Is that not potentially extremely dangerous, given that nothing like that happened during the whole of the cold war period? If we are to get a solution in the north, we have to look to building a moderate Sunni regime in Syria and Iraq. We may have to go back at the end of the war to redraw the boundaries drawn up by Sykes-Picot.
